  "articleSummary": "This tutorial provides a step-by-step guide for configuring UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall) on a Debian/Ubuntu Docker host to secure containerized applications. Key steps include installing ufw and nmap, setting default deny policies for incoming traffic, selectively allowing SSH, HTTP/HTTPS, and Docker-specific outbound rules, and forwarding external ports to Docker containers. The article emphasizes caution to avoid SSH lockout and recommends testing with nmap scans. The intended audience is system administrators or developers managing Docker hosts, and the tone is instructional with clear warnings and command examples.",
